abstract_summ: Aneurysms of internal carotid artery were mostly common (92.6%), especially in cavernous (35.1%) and in para-ophthalmic (40.3%) segments . 83 cases (61.9%) had wide-neck aneurysms, and 16 cases (11.9) had multiple aneurymysms . Endovascular treatment was successfully performed at rate of 94.8% .
